# Dotto Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Python (Modal.com serverless environment)
- Frontend: React / Next.js with Tailwind CSS
- AI Models: Fast-Whisper-Large (via Modal)
- Automation: n8n (for RAG and external workflows)

## Coding Standards
- Always prioritize modularity and clean, readable code.
- In Modal scripts: Always implement efficient resource management (use ffmpeg for audio extraction first).
- In Frontend: Use functional components, Tailwind for styling, and keep API calls clean.
- When generating code, always include basic error handling.

## Workflow
- When I ask for a feature, first explain the logic/architecture.
- Break down complex tasks into smaller, manageable steps.
- If a dependency is needed, suggest the exact installation command.